, England","Tunstall, Swale district, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tunstall, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Herstmonceux, Sussex, England":"Herstmonceux, Sussex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cromer","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Kromer   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. The surname <i>Cromer</i>, which is very rare in Germany, is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine); compare 2 below.","French: from an ancient Germanic personal name, <i>Hrodmar</i>, composed of the elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘renown, glory’ + <i>mār</i> ‘famous’. Compare 1 above.","Jewish: altered form of   Kromer  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kromer","meanings":["German (also <b>Krömer</b>): occupational name for a small retailer, a variant of <b>Krämer</b> (see   Kramer  ). Compare   Kroemer  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): occupational name for a small retailer, from Yiddish <i>krom</i> ‘small shop’ (compare 1 above)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir William Cromer was born in 1416, in Tunstall, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir William Cromer. He married Elizabeth Fiennes in 1440, in Herstmonceux, Sussex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 4 July 1450, in Tower of London, Middlesex, England, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1416–4 July 1450":"1416–4. juuli 1450","1416–1450":"1416–1450","1425–1459":"1425–1459","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1386–1434":"1386–1434","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","4 July 1450":"4. juuli 1450","1434":"1434","1386":"1386","1440":"1440","January 1434":"jaanuar 1434","1450":"1450","1505":"1505","1416":"1416","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, England","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Tower of London, Middlesex, England":"Tower of London, Middlesex, England","Tunstall, Swale district, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tunstall, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herstmonceux, Sussex, England":"Herstmonceux, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"1416–4 July 1450":"1416–4. heinäkuuta 1450","1416–1450":"1416–1450","1425–1459":"1425–1459","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1386–1434":"1386–1434","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","4 July 1450":"4. heinäkuuta 1450","1434":"1434","1386":"1386","1440":"1440","January 1434":"tammikuu 1434","1450":"1450","1505":"1505","1416":"1416","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, England","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Tower of London, Middlesex, England":"Tower of London, Middlesex, England","Tunstall, Swale district, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tunstall, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Herstmonceux, Sussex, England":"Herstmonceux, Sussex, England"},"fr":{"1416–4 July 1450":"1416–4 juillet 1450","1416–1450":"1416–1450","1425–1459":"1425–1459","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1386–1434":"1386–1434","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","4 July 1450":"4 juillet 1450","1434":"1434","1386":"1386","1440":"1440","January 1434":"janvier 1434","1450":"1450","1505":"1505","1416":"1416","Tunstall, Kent, England":"Tunstall, Kent, Angleterre","London, Middlesex, England":"Londres, Middlesex, Angleterre","Tower of London, Middlesex, England":"Tower of London, Middlesex, Angleterre","Tuns